news.title: Carpediem Capital invests Rs 100 crore in CorporatEdge
news.para: CorporatEdge plans to deploy Rs 350 crore in the next three years. It will unveil two centres, each spanning across 50,000 sq ft, in Q1 FY26 at World Trade Center (WTC) Nauroji Nagar, New Delhi, and Godrej Golf Course Road, Gurugram.

news.title: Jaipur: 900 traders protest after HC orders 19 buildings to be sealed
news.para: "All the establishments in these 19 buildings have proper commercial connections for electricity and water. Regular UD tax is collected from us, and all norms are followed by the traders.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Realtor loses Rs 2.29 crore in an alleged fraud
news.para: According to the complaint filed with the Detection of Crime Branch (DCB) police, Patel was introduced to the Ravals in early 2022 through a manager of a private bank.

news.title: Home sales in Toronto drops 28.5% in February 2025
news.para: Seasonally adjusted sales were down 28.5% on a month-over-month basis to 4,326 units after climbing 12.4% in January. Compared to February 2024, sales were down 27.4%.

news.title: Nashik civic body issues notices to 2,000 property tax dodgers
news.para: So far, notices have been issued to over 2,000 defaulters, asking them to clear their tax dues within 15 days. The NMC has over 1.5 lakh property tax defaulters with dues over Rs 250 crore.

news.title: Two firms to set up global capability centres in Indore
news.para: Two enterprises have announced intentions to establish GCCs in Indore, pledging to generate approximately 40,500 new employment opportunities in the region.

news.title: Environmental clearance delay leads to illegal sand mining in Rajasthan
news.para: Recently, Dotasra highlighted on X the brazenness of the mafia. He said, "In Rajasthan, courts, laws, and regulations are being openly flouted to facilitate illegal mining and the loot of sand.

news.title: NDMC attaches 13 properties in Delhi's Connaught Place over tax dues
news.para: Officials said that these included well-known establishments in blocks A, B, D and E, including restaurants, clothing shops and accessories outlets.

news.title: CBI books Jai Corporation and promoters in cheating and fraud case
news.para: The CBI is booked eight including Jai Corp Ltd., AnandJaikumar Jain, the Director/Promoter Jai Corp Limited, Parag Shantilal Parekh, Urban Infrastructure Venture Capital Ltd. and Urban Infrastructure Trustees Ltd. and unnamed shell companies and private trust based in India and overseas.

news.title: Noida: Stamp and registry department to open office on March 8, 9
news.para: Officials said the decision was taken as the financial year is ending this month and it has achieved only 80% of its revenue target of Rs 4,880 crore.

news.title: Hyderabad: GHMC asks Venkata Praneeth Developers to halt unauthorised construction
news.para: Landlords and farmers from Patancheru raised alarm regarding the illegal construction activities undertaken by Venkata Praneeth Developers.

news.title: Dues not paid, Sports City’s developers served notice in Noida
news.para: The dues include pending premiums, interest on premiums, penalty interest, lease rent, the 64.7% additional compensation amount and time extension fees.

news.title: Bankruptcy court allows 90 days extension to revive Lavasa Corporation
news.para: The planned city project is undergoing a fresh Corporate Insolvency Resolution Process (CIRP) after the National Company Law Tribunal directed to restart the whole process after the successful bidder failed to implement the approved resolution plan within the timeline.

news.title: Delhi HC declines immediate relief to Okhla slum dwellers
news.para: A bench of Chief Justice Devendra Upadhyay and Justice Tushar Rao Gedela declined to hear the appeal filed by the locals on Wednesday itself but indicated it would be automatically listed on Thursday if documents were in order.

news.title: Mumbai: MMRDA lodges FIR against illegal occupants of 1,336 Kurla homes
news.para: Last year, MMRDA had issued eviction notices to the illegal occupants. MMRDA had also sought more than Rs 35 cr in rental arrears with GST from them.

news.title: NCLT freezes Ansal API's bank accounts
news.para: This development marks a crucial step in the insolvency process of Ansal API, with further actions expected in the coming weeks. The receiver's team is also compiling records of home and plot bookings.

news.title: Bihar CM releases Rs 1,200 crore as first instalment of PMAY-Gramin
news.para: During the programme, rural development department (RDD) secretary, Lokesh Kumar Singh informed through a presentation that the state govt got a target of construction of 2,43,903 houses under the PMAY-G in Sept 2024 from the Centre.

news.title: Telangana RERA fines TMR Marvel's builder for deficit amenities
news.para: According to the complaint, Sravanthi entered into an agreement with the developers on Feb 5, 2018, to purchase a semi-finished villa.

news.title: Telangana RERA orders Padmasreekar Icon's builder to fix defects, pay fine
news.para: In its order dated March 1, the authority directed the builder to pay a penalty of 4.5 lakh and rectify defects in the flats at Padmasreekar Icon, Gajularamaram of Medchal-Malkajgiri.

news.title: Chennai civic body issues exhaustive guidelines to prevent construction pollution
news.para: In a preemptive effort, GCC has come out with exhaustive guidelines mandating builders to place barricades, cover construction sites with metal sheets to prevent dust from spilling, use anti-smog guns and to ensure vehicles carrying debris are covered with tarpaulin sheets.
